**Two tests. Contract + integration.**

**1. Contract test — `buildCart` output shape:**
```js
describe('buildCart', () => {
  const cart = { id: 'c1', items: [{ price: 10, qty: 2 }] };

  it('returns id, items, total', () => {
    const out = buildCart(cart);
    expect(out).toEqual({
      id: 'c1',
      items: [{ price: 10, qty: 2 }],
      total: 20,
    });
  });

  it('preserves items field', () => {
    expect(buildCart(cart)).toHaveProperty('items');
  });
});
```

**2. Integration test — POST /api/orders end-to-end:**
```js
describe('POST /api/orders', () => {
  it('creates order from cart with items', async () => {
    const res = await request(app)
      .post('/api/orders')
      .send({ cartId: 'c1' });
    expect(res.status).toBe(200);
    expect(res.body.items).toBeDefined();
  });
});
```

**Why both:** contract test catch shape regression fast at unit level. Integration test catch wiring break across handler + serializer.

**Bonus:** snapshot test on `buildCart` output — any shape change fail loud.

```js
it('matches shape snapshot', () => {
  expect(buildCart(cart)).toMatchSnapshot();
});
```

Pick contract + integration minimum. Snapshot optional.

